thread.title: Trade deficit widens in August
thread.title_full: Trade deficit widens in August | Business Spectator

author: Mitchell Neems
title: Trade deficit widens in August
text:
Australia's trade deficit has widened in August, against expectations of a slight narrowing.
According to figures from the Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) the nation's trade deficit widened a seasonally adjusted 11 per cent to $3.095 billion.
The result follows an upwardly revised deficit of $2.792bn in July.
The result fell well outside forecasts, with economists surveyed by Bloomberg expecting the trade deficit would narrow slightly to $2.4bn in the month.
Imports rose 1 per cent in the month, while exports were flat.
